column14: A new quest-journal would help identifying the current objectives of the game.
column15: Items need concrete values that indicate how much something changes after being applied. For example turning "Makes Digimon a bit full" into "Makes Digimon a bit full (+20 Food Points)".
column16: The game needs additional progress bars for food or toilet needs.
column17: The progressbar for happiness and discipline should not be divided into two separate progressbars.
column18: Health- and manapoints should be permanently displayed on the HUD.
column19: Items lost upon losing a heart should be shown to the player.
column20: There should be an indicator that shows how much time passes after training or other activities that take a certain amount of time.
column21: Buttons that can be pressed to interact should be displayed on the HUD.
column22: The clock should have a hand / pointer instead of a point indicating the current hour.
column23: Scolding should be removed completly from the game.
column24: A minimap should be implemented that helps navigating through the game world.
column25: The minimap should show additional information. For example where npcs
column26: food or the nearest toilet is.
column27: The player should be able to select a gender.
column28: It should be possible to give the character a new look.
column29: There should be more interactions during the battle.
column30: The battle could be a rhythm-based system.
column31: There should be an ingame tutorial instead of a manual.
